<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,736,974]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. S. Fernandes &amp; Salino" authorityYear="2014" box="[136,340,736,757]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis box="[136,340,736,757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Meniscium divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Maxon &amp; Morton 1938: 362) Jermy &amp; Walker (1985: 276)" authorityName="Jermy &amp; Walker" authorityPageNumber="276" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="Maxon &amp; Morton" baseAuthorityPageNumber="362" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[522,1246,736,758]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nesioticum">
<emphasis box="[522,658,736,757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">M. nesioticum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Maxon, W. R. &amp; Morton, C. V." box="[672,950,736,757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="347 - 376" refId="ref6839" refString="Maxon, W. R. &amp; Morton, C. V. (1938) The American species of Dryopteris subgenus Meniscium. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 65: 347 - 376. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 2481218" type="journal article" year="1938">
Maxon &amp; Morton 
<emphasis box="[852,950,736,757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">1938: 362</emphasis>
</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Jermy, A. C. &amp; Walker, T. G." box="[965,1246,736,758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="251 - 276" refId="ref6682" refString="Jermy, A. C. &amp; Walker, T. G. (1985) Cytotaxonomic studies of the ferns of Trinidad. Bulletin of the British Museum Natural History Botany 13 (2): 251 - 276." type="journal article" year="1985">Jermy &amp; Walker (1985: 276)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, with which it shares dimorphic fronds, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Smith &amp; Lellinger 1985: 918) R. S. Fernandes &amp; Salino" authorityName="R. S. Fernandes &amp; Salino" baseAuthorityName="Smith &amp; Lellinger" baseAuthorityPageNumber="918" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[411,1096,772,794]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cocleanum">
<emphasis box="[411,548,772,793]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">M. cocleanum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, A. R. &amp; Lellinger D. B." box="[561,846,772,794]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="916 - 930" refId="ref7736" refString="Smith, A. R. &amp; Lellinger D. B. (1985) New Tropical American Species of Thelypteris (Pteridophyta). Proceeding of the Biological Society of Washington 98 (4): 916 - 930." type="journal article" year="1985">Smith &amp; Lellinger 1985: 918</bibRefCitation>
) R.S.Fernandes &amp; Salino
</taxonomicName>
, with which it shares pinnae that are glabrous abaxially. It differs from these species mainly by the presence of 5–6 pinnae pairs, 5–6 rows of areoles between the costa and pinna margin in sterile pinnae and 3–4 areole rows in fertile pinnae, sori on the cross-veins, sori not confluent at maturity, and sporangial stalks with trichomes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
