<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1020,2091]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1452,158,544]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1848,1874]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Notes:—</emphasis>
In the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schreber" authorityYear="1791" box="[442,565,1849,1874]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[442,565,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Meniscium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only three species have dimorphic fronds— 
<taxonomicName authority="Kunze (1839: 44)" authorityName="Kunze" authorityPageNumber="44" authorityYear="1839" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophyllum">
<emphasis box="[1078,1370,1848,1874]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Meniscium macrophyllum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kunze, G." pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="44 - 45" refId="ref6746" refString="Kunze, G. (1839) 362. Meniscium macrophyllum. Flora 22 (1), Beiblatt 3: 44 - 45." type="journal article" year="1839">Kunze (1839: 44)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[278,449,1885,1910]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jermy &amp; Walker" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="Maxon &amp; Morton" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[278,445,1885,1910]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nesioticum">M. nesioticum</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. S. Fernandes &amp; Salino" authorityYear="2014" box="[514,664,1884,1910]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis box="[514,664,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">M. divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—and they all occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[954,1045,1884,1910]" name="Guyana" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Guyana</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kunze" authorityYear="1839" box="[1060,1356,1884,1910]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophyllum">
<emphasis box="[1060,1356,1884,1910]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Meniscium macrophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jermy &amp; Walker" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="Maxon &amp; Morton" baseAuthorityYear="1938" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nesioticum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">M. nesioticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinct from the new species in having acrostichoid sori and pilose abaxial surfaces of costae and veins. In addition, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kunze" authorityYear="1839" box="[270,467,1956,1982]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrophyllum">
<emphasis box="[270,467,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">M. macrophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has sterile pinnae 
<quantity box="[670,793,1956,1983]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.75" metricValueMax="7.8" metricValueMin="5.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="cm" value="6.75" valueMax="7.8" valueMin="5.7">5.7–7.8 cm</quantity>
wide, fertile pinnae 
<quantity box="[1020,1143,1956,1983]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.95" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="cm" value="2.95" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.7">2.7–3.2 cm</quantity>
wide, and oblong to elliptic pinnae. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jermy &amp; Walker" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="Maxon &amp; Morton" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[225,384,1993,2018]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nesioticum">
<emphasis box="[225,384,1993,2018]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">M. nesioticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 7–11 pinnae pairs, fertile pinnae with 6–13 areole rows between costae and margin, fertile lamina with curved trichomes on abaxial side of costae, sori usually appearing to cover the lamina (acrostichoid) and sporangia glabrous. In comparison, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. S. Fernandes &amp; Salino" authorityYear="2014" box="[540,686,2064,2090]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis box="[540,686,2064,2090]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">M. divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has sterile pinnae 
<quantity box="[897,1023,2064,2091]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="cm" value="3.0" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="2.4">2.4–3.6 cm</quantity>
wide, fertile pinnae 1.0– 
<quantity box="[1307,1382,2064,2091]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="cm" value="1.8">1.8 cm</quantity>
wide, and linear–lanceolate to oblong pinnae, as well as 5–6 pinnae pairs, fertile pinnae with 3–4 areole rows between costa and margin, fertile laminae glabrous abaxially, sori oblong, on the cross–veins, not confluent at maturity (Fig. 1A–D), and sporangia stalks with acicular trichomes (Fig. 3A).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Although with a distinct geographical distribution (
<collectingCountry box="[772,865,266,292]" name="Panama" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[878,1001,266,292]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1059,1179,266,293]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. S. Fernandes &amp; Salino" baseAuthorityName="Smith &amp; Lellinger" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[1199,1451,266,292]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cocleanum">
<emphasis box="[1199,1451,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Meniscium cocleanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. S. Fernandes &amp; Salino" authorityYear="2014" box="[340,486,302,329]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis box="[340,363,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[378,486,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having 
<emphasis box="[608,658,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">both</emphasis>
sides of laminar surface between the veins glabrous but differs by the presence of buds on the axils of the distal pinnae, 7–10 areole rows between costa and margin in fertile pinnae, and glabrous sporangia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,158,544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The spores have not been used to distinguish species within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schreber" authorityYear="1791" box="[870,993,411,436]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[870,993,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Meniscium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the past. However, they provide good characters, not only at the generic level (
<bibRefCitation author="Tryon, R. M. &amp; Tryon, A. F." box="[583,817,446,473]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" refId="ref8048" refString="Tryon, R. M. &amp; Tryon, A. F. (1982) Fern and allied plants, with special reference to Tropical America. Springer Verlag, New York, 857 pp. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4613 - 8162 - 4" type="book" year="1982">Tryon &amp; Tryon 1982</bibRefCitation>
) but also for separating closely related species. Spores of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. S. Fernandes &amp; Salino" authorityYear="2014" box="[136,281,482,508]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis box="[136,281,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">M. divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are echinulate (Fig. 4C–D), cristate-reticulate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jermy &amp; Walker" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="Maxon &amp; Morton" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[828,986,483,508]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nesioticum">
<emphasis box="[828,986,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">M. nesioticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 4E–F) and winged in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. S. Fernandes &amp; Salino" baseAuthorityName="Smith &amp; Lellinger" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[1293,1451,482,508]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Thelypteridaceae" genus="Meniscium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cocleanum">
<emphasis box="[1293,1451,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">M. cocleanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 4A–B).
</paragraph>
